      "text": "Every feature checks out. Here's what's in `game.html`:\n\n## game.html — Pokémon Gen 3 Style HTML5 Battle\n\n**1,518 lines, single file, zero dependencies.** Open it in any browser.\n\n### What's inside\n\n**Map Exploration (Phase 1)**\n- 20×15 tile map with grass, roads, tall grass, trees, flowers — all procedurally drawn\n- Player character (red hat, blue shirt — Gen3 protagonist vibes) with arrow-key grid movement and smooth walking animation\n- NPC Rival standing on the road with a `!` indicator when you're nearby\n- Press **Z** near the NPC → dialog with character-by-character text printing\n\n**Battle System (Phase 2)**\n- **GBA transition**: screen flash → mosaic/pixelate → fade to black\n- **Battle scene**: sky gradient, green ground, elliptical platforms, Charizard (back sprite) vs Mewtwo (front sprite)\n- **Sprites**: loaded from PokeAPI (`pokemon/back/6.png`, `pokemon/150.png`), colored rectangle fallback on failure\n- **HP bars**: trapezoidal Gen3-style frames, lerp animation, green→yellow→red color shifts, numeric HP on player side\n- **Action panel**: Fight / Bag / Pokémon / Run (2×2 grid), move select with type colors and PP display\n- **Gen3 damage formula**: `((2*Lv/5+2)*Power*A/D)/50+2` × Critical(2×, 6.25%) × STAB(1.5×) × Type effectiveness × Random(0.85–1.0)\n- **Physical/Special by type**: Physical = Normal/Fighting/Flying/Poison/Ground/Rock/Bug/Ghost/Steel; Special = Fire/Water/Grass/Electric/Psychic/Ice/Dragon/Dark\n- **Full type chart**: 17 types with immunities, resistances, super-effectives\n- **Accuracy checks**: moves can miss based on their accuracy stat\n- **Enemy AI**: prioritizes super-effective moves → KO potential → highest power\n- **Hit feedback**: shake + flash on hit, extra flash on critical\n- **Faint animation**: slide-down + fade-out\n- **All text**: character-by-character printing with Z to fast-forward/advance\n\n### Controls\n| Key | Action |\n|-----|--------|\n| Arrow keys | Move (map) / Navigate menus (battle) |\n| Z / Enter | Interact / Confirm |\n| X / Backspace | Back (move select → action menu) |",
